JOHANNESBURG - Emergency personnel had their hands full on Friday morning as heavy rains continued to pour across Gauteng. Areas affected by flash flooding have been closed to traffic. READ: Widespread traffic chaos in Gauteng following heavy rains Several roads have been flooded in some parts of Pretoria and a road has also collapsed near the Laudium area. There were also reports of several families having been evacuated in townships around Tshwane. eNCA